article.description: Freshman Emese Hof set season highs with 26 points and 14 rebounds in her first start to help No. 23 Miami beat Indiana 89-75 on Sunday night in the Florida Sunshine Classic.
article.headline: No. 23 Miami women beat Indiana in Florida Sunshine Classic
article.linkText: No. 23 Miami women beat Indiana in Florida Sunshine Classic
article.story:
WINTER PARK, Fla. --  Freshman Emese Hof set season highs with 26 points and 14 rebounds in her first start to help No. 23 Miami beat Indiana 89-75 on Sunday night in the Florida Sunshine Classic.

Hof was 10 of 13 from the field and 6 of 7 at the line.

Trailing 40-39 at halftime, Miami opened the third quarter with a 9-0 run, capped by Adrienne Motley's 3-pointer from the wing. Indiana scored the next seven but Miami answered with a 16-4 spurt, including 3-pointers by Laura Cornelius and Michelle Woods, for a 64-50 lead.

Indiana pulled to 79-71, but Keyona Hayes' one-handed tip-in highlighted a 6-0 run for a 14-point lead with four minutes left.

Motley finished with 18 points for Miami (11-1). Cornelius made a career-high four 3-pointers and scored 12 points.

Tyra Buss led Indiana (7-3) with 28 points, seven rebounds and four assists. She made three of the Hoosiers' nine 3-pointers.
